    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-11-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-11-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="334"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d334">
                <head>334. Telegram 1036 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d334fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/11–255. Confidential;
                        Priority; Limited Distribution.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-11-02"
                            >November 2, 1955, 2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d334-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d334-1"/>
                <p>1036. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>. Reference: Deptel
                    1078.</p>
                <p>Presume Department will request UK instruct <persName corresp="#p_OC_1"
                        >O’Neill</persName> immediately attempt arrange visit to Downey. I do not
                    see how any question priority is involved and would hope <persName
                        corresp="#p_OC_1">O’Neill</persName> would in interview particularly attempt
                    test CHICOM regulation on “discussion case in which prisoner involved”.</p>
                <p>In this connection Department and <persName corresp="#p_OC_1">O’Neill</persName>
                    should have in mind usual Communist (as well as former Japanese and some
                    European) practice of keeping prisoner incommunicado until “investigation” case
                    completed. As Downey has been tried and sentenced such consideration should
                    under any circumstances no longer apply his case. Also should note fact censor
                    passed Downey’s letter specifically asking “to discuss his case”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
